\end{center}
\begin{abstract}
We discuss a possible exact equivalence of the Abelian
Higgs model and a scalar theory of a magnetic vortex
field in 2+1 dimensions. The vortex model has a
current - current interaction and can be viewed as a
strong coupling limit of a massive vector theory.
The fixed point structure of the theory is discussed
and mapped into fixed points of the Higgs model.
\end{abstract}

\vspace{50pt}
\
\newline
